  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2010-11-17",
    "date": "2010-11-26T20:11:17Z",
    "text": "Consumer Protection Act of 2010 - Provides that it shall not be a defense to a tort claim in any U.S. court that a manufacturer of a product has fulfilled that manufacturer's duty of care when providing all of the necessary information to a learned intermediary, who then interacts with the consumer of the product.\n\nDefines a \"learned intermediary\" as a person licensed under applicable state or federal law to advise a consumer whether or not to use the product in question."
  },
